    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with a lid with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turmeric-basa-and-vietnamese-style-rice-broth/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate your<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Dissolve your<strong> pho broth paste</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]<strong> </span>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>pho stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turmeric-basa-and-vietnamese-style-rice-broth/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel your<strong> carrot[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turmeric-basa-and-vietnamese-style-rice-broth/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>basa fillets</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>turmeric cornflour</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped basa</strong> to the <strong>turmeric</strong> <strong>cornflour</strong> and give everything a good mix up until fully coated, then set aside for later \u2013 these are your <strong>coated basa</strong> <strong>pieces</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turmeric-basa-and-vietnamese-style-rice-broth/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> grated ginger</strong>, <strong>sliced shallot</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>ground coriander</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant \u2013 this is your <strong>ginger & shallot mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turmeric-basa-and-vietnamese-style-rice-broth/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>ginger & shallot mix</strong> to the pot with the brown rice (reserve the pan!), then add the<strong> pho stock</strong>,<strong> lime leaf[ves]</strong>,<strong> chopped green beans </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium-high and cook, covered<strong> </strong>for an initial 2-3 min or until the green beans are tender</p><p>Once tender, add the <strong>spinach</strong> and<strong> carrot ribbons </strong>and cook, covered, for a final 1-2 min or until the spinach has wilted \u2013 this is your <strong>Vietnamese-style rice broth</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turmeric-basa-and-vietnamese-style-rice-broth/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a medium-high heat with 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated basa pieces </strong>and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until golden and crisp \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy turmeric basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-turmeric-basa-and-vietnamese-style-rice-broth/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Vietnamese-style rice broth</strong> in bowls, topped with the <strong>crispy turmeric basa</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
